overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for
  data access, and an authentication system. The approach involved updating the
  application's demographic data structure to align with the SOW, creating a new
  Prisma model for questionnaire responses, and developing API endpoints for
  saving and retrieving data. A simple admin dashboard was built, featuring a
  login page, a table to display responses, and a CSV export function. The
  authentication mechanism was initially a custom session management system but
  was later streamlined to leverage Next.js middleware for more efficient route
  protection using a basic cookie. The database setup instructions were
  provided, and the implementation was successfully tested in the browser,
  confirming questionnaire submission, admin login, and data persistence.
